288
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:53,020
Someone as amazing as you 

289
00:15:53,020 --> 00:15:55,520
would never fall for me. 

290
00:15:55,950 --> 00:15:58,250
If I had thought about it for a second, I'd know. 

291
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:01,520
Somehow, I just got the wrong idea.  

292
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,230
How embarrassing! 

293
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:06,460
So, what should we do now? 

294
00:16:06,460 --> 00:16:08,600
Are you going to kill me? 

295
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:11,150
I don't have a gun right now anyway. 

296
00:16:14,950 --> 00:16:17,320
I won't. 

297
00:16:18,350 --> 00:16:19,770
Let's get married. 

298
00:16:20,350 --> 00:16:21,700
What? 

299
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:30,540
I want you to marry me. 

300
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:39,220
At first, I was going to kill you. 

301
00:16:39,220 --> 00:16:41,070
That was the order I was told to. 

302
00:16:42,190 --> 00:16:44,480
But I got interested in you. 

303
00:16:45,950 --> 00:16:51,670
You're a top-class assassin and yet you're just a normal girl.

304
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:02,100
Before I knew it you were all I could think about.  

305
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:22,470
I was raised as an assassin and that's all I've ever known.   

306
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:28,490
But, you know, my dream is...

307
00:17:32,990 --> 00:17:36,160
...to be normal. 

308
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:40,940
To get normally married, work a normal job... 

309
00:17:40,940 --> 00:17:43,810
And normally raise kids. 

310
00:17:45,580 --> 00:17:48,100
If you're with me, that dream can come true. 

311
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:53,150
We're both assassins, you know.  

312
00:17:53,150 --> 00:17:56,270
We'll both quit, of course. 

313
00:17:57,180 --> 00:17:59,750
I'll give my client a fake corpse.  

314
00:17:59,750 --> 00:18:02,230
That way, they'll think K is dead.  

315
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,820
It'll be fine. 

316
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:14,700
I promise it'll work. 

317
00:18:15,950 --> 00:18:18,770
I'll make K disappear. 

318
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:30,920
Wait, let me process this for a second. 

319
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:33,950
Yesterday, you went to his place for the first time. 

320
00:18:33,950 --> 00:18:34,810
Yeah...

321
00:18:34,810 --> 00:18:37,020
And he proposed to you there. 

322
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:39,060
Yeah...

323
00:18:39,060 --> 00:18:41,870
Sorry, but I don't see any problem at all. 

324
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:44,740
I mean, I did say it's too soon. 

325
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:47,230
But you said it yourself that you want to get married.

326
00:18:49,150 --> 00:18:51,950
But there's a lot going on. 

327
00:18:51,950 --> 00:18:53,900
What do you mean, "a lot"? 

328
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:57,100
If I don't understand that part, I can't help you. 

329
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:59,190
About that... 

330
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:01,710
Umm... 

331
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:16,310
Actually, I'm an assassin.  

332
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:18,620
And... 

333
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:20,400
He's an assassin too, so I thought,  

334
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:22,520
it's lucky of me, right? 

335
00:19:22,860 --> 00:19:26,770
But when we get married he wants me to quit being an assassin.   

336
00:19:26,770 --> 00:19:32,840
And if I refuse, he might need to kill me. 

337
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:35,570
But actually... 

338
00:19:36,170 --> 00:19:41,000
I'm supposed to kill him too... 

339
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:44,560
What kind of metaphor is this? 

340
00:19:44,940 --> 00:19:48,230
Ah... Well...  

341
00:19:50,430 --> 00:19:52,800
If it were me, I'd quit. 

342
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:55,080
I mean if I don't, I'll get killed, right? 

343
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:56,310
By an assassin. 

344
00:19:58,010 --> 00:20:00,020
But if... 

345
00:20:00,020 --> 00:20:02,650
I stop being an assassin...

346
00:20:02,650 --> 00:20:04,520
What will I become? 

347
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:06,530
Yeah... 

348
00:20:06,530 --> 00:20:08,690
Seriously, what is this metaphor? 

349
00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:48,880
Excuse me... 

350
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:49,810
Sakurai. 

351
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,870
If... 

352
00:20:52,870 --> 00:20:54,270
If I quit... 

353
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:04,940
That was croaky scary. 

354
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:08,140
I'm sorry about that! 

355
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:11,820
Um... 

356
00:21:11,820 --> 00:21:14,310
If I quit... 

357
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:16,870
Would you...

358
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:21,150
...have more fun at work?  

359
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:25,860
I'll kill you. 

360
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:33,350
I never thought about fun in work... 

361
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:36,900
...not until recently. 

362
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:46,470
Hey, hitmen!

363
00:21:46,470 --> 00:21:48,450
Where are you?! Hey!

364
00:21:48,450 --> 00:21:49,350
Let's go kill them! 

365
00:21:50,630 --> 00:21:51,520
Yes, Sir!

366
00:22:39,420 --> 00:22:40,560
Welcome. 

367
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:46,810
This looks terrible. 

368
00:22:46,810 --> 00:22:47,750
Yeah.

369
00:22:47,750 --> 00:22:49,720
It's not personal. 

370
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:51,850
Meaning? 

371
00:22:51,850 --> 00:22:53,440
The company uses pro assassins. 

372
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,730
They get the job done in one hit. 

373
00:22:55,730 --> 00:22:57,620
The target is a pro too. 

374
00:22:57,620 --> 00:22:58,560
K? 

375
00:22:58,560 --> 00:23:00,650
Their style is different. 

376
00:23:00,650 --> 00:23:03,060
That was meant to look like a warning. 

377
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:05,480
It's an internal dispute. 

378
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,350
Can you tell the gun they used? 

379
00:23:09,880 --> 00:23:12,080
Yeah, I can tell right away. 

380
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,350
Forensics! 

381
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:14,980
You're kidding. 

382
00:23:15,150 --> 00:23:16,990
It was the same gun! 

383
00:23:16,990 --> 00:23:17,750
Huh? 

384
00:23:17,750 --> 00:23:19,310
The same as the one who attacked Nishino! 

385
00:23:19,310 --> 00:23:21,520
He killed someone and ran! 

386
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:23,310
Nishino is not answering her phone! 

387
00:23:23,850 --> 00:23:25,610
So, tell me her addre... 

388
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,190
Damn... 

389
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:30,230
Damn it! 

390
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:39,980
Hurry, Sakurai! 

391
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:50,480
Looks like you're unarmed. 

392
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,310
Which means... 

393
00:23:55,070 --> 00:23:57,690
Can I take that as a good sign? 

394
00:23:59,220 --> 00:24:00,750
Hosomi. 

395
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:02,100
Yeah? 

396
00:24:02,620 --> 00:24:05,120
Hosomi. 

397
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:06,980
What do you like about me? 

398
00:24:09,090 --> 00:24:10,870
Let's see... 

399
00:24:12,830 --> 00:24:17,230
I like how normally cute you are, I guess. 

400
00:24:19,250 --> 00:24:21,950
Can you call it normal and cute when I am a hitman? 

401
00:24:21,950 --> 00:24:23,690
Nishino. 

402
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,870
I really do love you. 

403
00:24:33,350 --> 00:24:34,800
It's okay. 

404
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:39,100
You and I can have a normal, 
happy life together. 

405
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:44,370
What even is "normal"? 

406
00:24:48,450 --> 00:24:50,750
The "normal" I know

407
00:24:50,750 --> 00:24:53,770
is totally exhausting. 

408
00:24:54,620 --> 00:24:57,150
You have to squeeze into packed trains. 

409
00:24:57,150 --> 00:24:59,860
You have to deal with gropers, and it's scary. 

410
00:24:59,860 --> 00:25:03,080
You can't even kill your power harassing boss.  

411
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:06,150
Even if you have a baby... 

412
00:25:06,150 --> 00:25:07,820
If they cry on the train, 

413
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:09,900
some jerk will yell at you. 

414
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:12,330
Even if you work at a store,

415
00:25:12,330 --> 00:25:14,350
if some weirdo picks a fight with you, 

416
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:19,900
even when it's not your fault, you still have to apologize and say "I'm sorry, I'm sorry."  

417
00:25:23,020 --> 00:25:24,690
Hosomi... 

418
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:29,270
Can you actually live that "normal" life? 

419
00:25:33,750 --> 00:25:35,190
It's because... 

420
00:25:36,850 --> 00:25:39,370
I couldn't do it. 

421
00:25:40,020 --> 00:25:42,000
That's why I've come this far. 

422
00:25:47,990 --> 00:25:50,560
Nishino... 

423
00:25:53,710 --> 00:25:56,530
My happiness is... 

424
00:25:59,950 --> 00:26:04,710
...this life as an assassin. 

425
00:26:41,550 --> 00:26:43,970
I really loved you...

426
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:19,510
You should have known already... 

427
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,990
If you'd paid more attention... 

428
00:27:25,740 --> 00:27:29,060
You would've known I was gonna kill you...

429
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:40,850
At least when you're gonna kill me... 

430
00:27:42,930 --> 00:27:46,920
Look at me closely! 

431
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:55,550
Okay, got it. 

432
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:58,400
Leave the rest to me. 

433
00:27:59,420 --> 00:28:01,450
Nishino. 

434
00:28:03,370 --> 00:28:05,440
Maybe he wanted you

435
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:08,150
to be the one to kill him. 

436
00:28:38,650 --> 00:28:40,110
Don't think too much about it. 

437
00:28:41,050 --> 00:28:42,400
Huh? 

438
00:28:43,690 --> 00:28:46,600
You just did what you had to do. 

439
00:28:58,230 --> 00:29:00,330
Aaaah! 

440
00:29:01,090 --> 00:29:02,320
Idiot! 

441
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:04,250
Idiot, idiot! 

442
00:29:04,250 --> 00:29:06,350
Like I'd die so easily! 

443
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,660
I am...! 

444
00:29:09,660 --> 00:29:11,300
The assassin...!

445
00:29:11,300 --> 00:29:15,400
Kanako Nishino! 

446
00:29:17,050 --> 00:29:18,310
Sakurai! 

447
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:21,950
Next stop, karaoke! 

448
00:29:23,050 --> 00:29:24,400
I'll kill you! 

449
00:29:35,620 --> 00:29:38,470
You could just went home for today, at least. 

450
00:29:42,980 --> 00:29:45,420
It turned out okay, huh? 

451
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:48,350
Nishino is safe.

452
00:29:49,450 --> 00:29:51,080
Yeah. 

453
00:29:51,450 --> 00:29:53,480
To think I thought she was weak. 

454
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:58,150
Nishino is strong. 

455
00:29:59,780 --> 00:30:01,620
I can tell. 

456
00:30:01,620 --> 00:30:06,400
 She said she's fine while dumping you over a call after all.

457
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:13,230
Well... 

458
00:30:13,230 --> 00:30:17,500
Someone out there probably likes a predictable,   

459
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:20,150
simple-minded guy like you somewhere.  

460
00:30:20,150 --> 00:30:21,950
Yeah... 

461
00:30:21,950 --> 00:30:24,730
Nishino said something similar. 

462
00:30:25,570 --> 00:30:27,480
That she was closer than I thought. 

463
00:30:35,650 --> 00:30:37,380
What's this? What are they? 

464
00:30:38,740 --> 00:30:39,770
What's wrong?

465
00:30:39,770 --> 00:30:44,800
From now on, please take care of me

